value.value: The deep parotid lymph nodes are lymph nodes found below the parotid gland. The afferents of the subparotid glands drain the nasal part of the pharynx and the posterior parts of the nasal cavities. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

The preauricular deep parotid lymph nodes (anterior auricular glands or preauricular glands), from one to three in number, lie immediately in front of the tragus. Their afferents drain the lateral surface of the auricula and the skin of the adjacent part of the temporal region; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.
The infra-auricular deep parotid lymph nodes are a group of lymph nodes found underneath the ear.

The submental lymph nodes (or suprahyoid) are situated between the anterior bellies of the Digastrici. Their afferents drain the central portions of the lower lip and floor of the mouth and the apex of the tongue. Their efferents pass partly to the submandibular lymph nodes and partly to a gland of the deep cervical group situated on the internal jugular vein at the level of the cricoid cartilage.
A lymph node that is part of a hindlimb.
A lymph node that is part of a forelimb.
The infrapatellar fat pad, also known as Hoffa's fat pad, is a cylindrical piece of fat that is situated under and behind the patella bone within the knee.
The thoracic wall (or chest wall) is the boundary of the thoracic cavity. The bony portion is known as the thoracic cage. However, the wall also includes muscle, skin, and fascia.
A vertebral arch joint that is part of a cervical region of vertebral column.
A capillary that is part of a lung.
The circumference of the base of the glans forms a rounded projecting border, the corona of the glans penis, overhanging a deep retroglandular sulcus, behind which is the neck of the penis.
A breast that is part of a male organism.

Central part of body of vertebra

value.value: Subdivision of thorax which is anterior to the plane of the posterior boundary of the middle mediastinum.

The intersection of the frontal and two nasal bones of the human skull. Its manifestation on the visible surface of the face is a distinctly depressed area directly between the eyes, just superior to the bridge of the nose.
A compact bone tissue that is part of a bone tissue of long bone.
A compact bone tissue that is part of a diaphysis.
An epiphyseal plate that is part of a radius bone.

label.value: proximal interphalangeal joint of little finger
Proximal interphalangeal joint of little finger

value.value: The palmar branch of the median nerve is a branch of the median nerve which arises at the lower part of the forearm and innervates skin of proximal central palm and thenar eminence.
Subdivision of thorax which includes all structures from the skin to the costal pleura. Examples: There is only one chest wall.
A zone of the frontal bone that connects the supraorbital rirdges.
The line of junction between the horizontal parts of the palatine bones that extends from both sides of the skull to form the posterior part of the hard palate.
A strand of hair that is part of a head.
A strand of hair that is part of a trunk.
A hole in the diaphragm through which the esophagus passes.
The central point on the posterior surface of the lens.

label.value: Skin of orbital part of face

value.value: A zone of skin in the periorbital region of the face.
The midline prominence of the nose, extending from the nasal root to the tip.

On the pinna, a curved prominence of cartilage, parallel with and in front of the helix, is called the antihelix, also known as the anthelix; this divides above into two crura, the crura antihelicis, between which is a triangular depression, the fossa triangularis.
The antitragus is a feature of human ear anatomy. It is a small tubercle that points anteriorly. It is separated from the tragus by the intertragic notch.
A zone of skin that is part of a forehead.
An incisor tooth that is part of a primary dentition.

The zygomatic process of the maxilla (malar process) is a rough triangular eminence, situated at the angle of separation of the anterior, zygomatic, and orbital surfaces. In front it forms part of the anterior surface. Behind it is concave, and forms part of the infratemporal fossa. Above it is rough and serrated for articulation with the zygomatic bone. Below it presents the prominent arched border which marks the division between the anterior and infratemporal surfaces.
A stroma that is part of a liver.
A collagenous capsule covering the external surface of the liver.
A lymph node that is part of a bronchus.
The vaginal fornix that is behind the cervix. It is close to the recto-uterine pouch.
The vaginal fornix that is front of the cervix. It is close to the vesico-uterine pouch.
